definitions.definition: ( music ) A percussive musical instrument spanned with a thin covering on at least one end for striking , forming an acoustic chamber ; a membranophone .
examples: He's playing the piano and she's playing the drums !
Replace the drum unit of your printer .

definitions.definition: A barrel or large cylindrical container for liquid transport and storage .
examples: The restaurant ordered ketchup in 50-gallon drums .

definitions.definition: ( architecture ) The encircling wall that supports a dome or cupola .
( architecture ) Any of the cylindrical blocks that make up the shaft of a pillar .
( Australia slang ) A tip ; a piece of information .

definitions.definition: ( now rare ) A small hill or ridge of hills.

definitions.definition: ( now historical ) A social gathering or assembly held in the evening . [from 18th c.]
( slang , chiefly UK ) A person 's home ; a house or other building, especially when insalubrious ; a tavern , a brothel . [from 19th c.]
